there's many ways to do intros:

Game (Object) -&gt; Script (Tab) -&gt; 'start' Script -&gt; (your intro scripts)
<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://docs.textadventures.co.uk/quest/guides/character_creation.html">http://docs.textadventures.co.uk/quest/ ... ation.html</a><!-- m -->

simply use your 'room' Room Object, as your 'intro' room.

Turnscripts, Timers, and etc... scripting methods

and etc etc etc creative ways (that I can't think of) to do an intro (with infinite code design methods).

------------

the two super scripts:

<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://docs.textadventures.co.uk/quest/scripts/set.html">http://docs.textadventures.co.uk/quest/scripts/set.html</a><!-- m -->
